header.gameNote: TOP OF THE WORLD CLASSIC AT FAIRBANKS AK

article.headline: Weber State 66, Troy 61
article.story: FAIRBANKS, Alaska (AP) -- Arturas Valeika scored 15 points and grabbed 12 rebounds and Weber State defeated Troy 66-61 Saturday in the semifinals of the BP Top of the World Classic. The Wildcats (3-0) led the entire second half and withstood a late rally to hold off the Trojans (2-2). Juan Pablo Silveira's 3-pointer with 45 seconds left in the first half broke a 30-30 tie and gave Weber State the lead for good. In the second half, the Wildcats pushed the lead to 50-36 with just under 12 minutes to play. Troy's Sammy Sharp cut the lead to 58-54 with a jumper and a free throw with 5:30 remaining. Troy had a chance to close the gap to one point with eight seconds left but Jerome Odem missed a long 3-pointer. Sharp finished with 15 points and 12 rebounds. Odem added with 12 points. David Patten had 12 points for the Wildcats. Weber State shot 45 percent for the game and picked up 22 points from the bench. Troy, which has led Division I teams the last three years on 3-pointers made per game, shot just 7-for-26 from behind the arc.
